` from earlier versions, but I'm not certain if `PascalCase` exists as a built-in policy. Since the user mentioned .NET 11, which is beyond my training data, it's possible this was added, so I should test it by creating and running the project to see if the API is available. I need to check what .NET SDK is actually available in the environment before committing to `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase`, then build the project and see if it works.","outputTokens":1232,"requestId":"6C03:78DEC:17F005:1C17DA:69FA8FD2"},"id":"08dd5838-5d40-4393-b865-63ce112360a5","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:40.363Z","parentId":"7cdba734-02a9-4b32-b898-c18217b402f7"}
